        I_AM_AFRAID_YOUR_PURSE_IS_A_TRIFLE                                                          = 10224,  -- I am afraid your purse is a trifle light today...
        MOST_EXCELLENT_I_SHALL_NOW_PROCEED_TO_ASK                                                   = 10225,  -- Most excellent. I shall now proceed to ask you several questions.
        MY_DIVINATIONS_FOLLOW_A_SOMEWHAT_UNORTHODOX_PROCESS_ANSWER                                  = 10226,  -- My divinations follow a somewhat unorthodox process. Answer truthfully and all shall be revealed.
        WHAT_IS_DESTINY                                                                             = 10227,  -- What is destiny?
        DESTINY_IS_SOMETHING_THAT_IS_IMMUTABLE_ONE_FORGES                                           = 10228,  -- Destiny is something that... Is immutable. One forges for oneself. Is unknowable.
        DOES_THE_ACCOMPLISHMENT_OF_A_GOAL_REQUIRE_SACRIFICE                                         = 10229,  -- Does the accomplishment of a goal require sacrifice and hardship?
        DO_GOALS_REQUIRE_SACRIFICE_NOT_IF_YOU_THINK                                                 = 10230,  -- Do goals require sacrifice? Not if you think hard enough. Occasionally. Absolutely.
        YOU_HOLD_IN_YOUR_HANDS_A_FORBIDDEN_SCROLL                                                   = 10231,  -- You hold in your hands a forbidden scroll. Reading it will bring you untold wisdom, but cost all that you own.
        DO_YOU_READ_THE_SCROLL_THROW_THE_SCROLL                                                     = 10232,  -- Do you... Read the scroll? Throw the scroll away? Burn the scroll?
        IF_THE_LOSS_OF_ONE_LIFE_WOULD_SAVE                                                          = 10233,  -- If the loss of one life would save ten thousand, would you offer yourself without hesitation?
        OFFER_YOURSELF_OFFER_ANOTHER_I_HAVE_NO_SUCH                                                 = 10234,  -- Offer yourself? Offer another... I have no such courage. Without hesitation.
        WOULD_YOU_CHOOSE_A_TUMULTUOUS_LIFE_WHERE_FAME                                               = 10235,  -- Would you choose a tumultuous life where fame or fortune were attainable, or a tranquil life where both were forever beyond your reach?
        WHICH_DO_YOU_CHOOSE_A_CHAOTIC_LIFE_A                                                        = 10236,  -- Which do you choose? A chaotic life. A tranquil life. A mix of both.
        YOU_STAND_ON_THE_PRECIPICE_BETWEEN_LIFE_AND                                                 = 10237,  -- You stand on the precipice between life and death. Would you choose to live life as a beast if it would save you from falling into the shadowy abyss of the underworld?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_DO_IF_IT_KEEPS_ME                                                               = 10238,  -- What do you do? If it keeps me from dying... Fall, and keep my humanity. Embrace life as a beast.
        A_COMPANION_IN_BATTLE_TURNS_AGAINST_YOU_RAISING                                             = 10239,  -- A companion in battle turns against you, raising a weapon to attack.
        DO_YOU_BRACE_FOR_THE_BLOW_TRY_TO                                                            = 10240,  -- Do you... Brace for the blow? Try to reason with him? Cut him down?
        A_LOVED_ONE_IS_AFFLICTED_WITH_A_TERRIBLE                                                    = 10241,  -- A loved one is afflicted with a terrible illness and has little time left to live. You are asked to end that life by your own hand.
        DO_YOU_SEEK_A_CURE_LEAVE_THE_WORLD                                                          = 10242,  -- Do you... Seek a cure? Leave the world together? Grant the request?
        YOU_ARE_IN_THE_MIDST_OF_A_FIERCE                                                            = 10243,  -- You are in the midst of a fierce battle. The enemy lying at your feet was once a friend. His breath is ragged and weak.
        DO_YOU_TEND_TO_HIS_WOUNDS_END_HIS                                                           = 10244,  -- Do you... Tend to his wounds? End his pain? Ignore your old friend?
        A_SUPERIOR_TO_WHOM_YOU_OWE_A_GREAT                                                          = 10245,  -- A superior to whom you owe a great debt orders you to act in a way that violates your sense of justice.
        DO_YOU_TRY_TO_REMOVE_HIM_FROM_POWER                                                         = 10246,  -- Do you... Try to remove him from power? Carry out the order? Follow your sense of justice?
        THANK_YOU_FOR_YOUR_PATIENCE_THE_ANSWERS_YOU                                                 = 10247,  -- Thank you for your patience. The answers you have provided will be most helpful in my divination. Let us look upon what has been revealed...
        I_SEE_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_SKYSERPENT_IT                                                       = 10248,  -- I see the symbol of the Skyserpent. It suggests spending some time away from battle.
        FOR_A_CHANGE_OF_PACE_WHY_NOT_TRY                                                            = 10249,  -- For a change of pace, why not try your hand at harvesting in the Wajaom Woodlands or Bhaflau Thickets?
        YOU_MAY_MAKE_AN_UNEXPECTED_DISCOVERY                                                        = 10250,  -- You may make an unexpected discovery.
        I_SEE_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_FLAMESERPENT_IT                                                     = 10251,  -- I see the symbol of the Flameserpent. It suggests you take an aggressive stance and not shy away from a challenge.
        PERHAPS_YOU_MIGHT_TRY_VISITING_THE_COMMISSIONS_AGENCY                                       = 10252,  -- Perhaps you might try visiting the Commissions Agency. A substantial reward could be yours for the taking.
        I_SEE_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_GALESERPENT_IT                                                      = 10253,  -- I see the symbol of the Galeserpent. It suggests a loss in the near future...
        EVEN_I_CANNOT_PREDICT_WHAT_THIS_LOSS_MAY                                                    = 10254,  -- Even I cannot predict what this loss may entail. You would do well to pay close attention to your possessions.
        I_SEE_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_STONESERPENT_IT                                                     = 10255,  -- I see the symbol of the Stoneserpent. It suggests you will receive a boon from the earth.
        A_BOON_FROM_THE_EARTH_AH_YES_A                                                              = 10256,  -- A boon from the earth...? Ah yes, a stint at mining may prove beneficial. All signs point towards Mount Zhayolm...
        I_SEE_THE_SYMBOL_OF_THE_SPRINGSERPENT_IT                                                    = 10257,  -- I see the symbol of the Springserpent. It suggests a sojourn to the sea.
        YES_A_TRANQUIL_JOURNEY_ON_THE_WAVES_REPLACE                                                 = 10258,  -- Yes, a tranquil journey on the waves. Replace your weapon with a fishing pole and fate will smile upon you.
        MY_DIVINATION_IS_OVER_I_TRUST_YOU_ARE                                                       = 10259,  -- My divination is over. I trust you are satisfied?
        AS_DIVINING_IS_MY_STOCK_IN_TRADE_IT                                                         = 10260,  -- As divining is my stock in trade, it may hardly surprise you to know that I believe destiny to be an ever flowing river of possibilities.
        YET_THERE_ARE_ALSO_THOSE_WHO_SEE_DESTINY                                                    = 10261,  -- Yet there are also those who see destiny as immutable and inescapable. Which do you believe, I wonder...?
        BUT_I_DIGRESS_IF_YOU_DESIRE_TO_HEAR                                                         = 10262,  -- ...But I digress. If you desire to hear my divinations again, return here after one full cycle of the sun.
        MAY_THE_TRUE_SERPENT_OF_WALAHRA_HOLD_YOU                                                    = 10263,  -- May the True Serpent of Walahra hold you firmly in its coils...
        YOU_PAY_1000_GIL_FOR_THE_DIVINATION                                                         = 10264,  -- You pay 1000 gil for the divination.
        SKY_FLAME_GALE_STONE_AND_SPRING_I_SEE                                                       = 10265,  -- Sky, Flame, Gale, Stone, and Spring. I see all five serpent symbols... This sign heralds a turning point in your destiny.
        A_TIME_WILL_COME_WHEN_YOU_MUST_CHOOSE                                                       = 10266,  -- A time will come when you must choose one of two paths. The road you walk will be entirely up to you...
        EVEN_I_CANNOT_ASCERTAIN_WHAT_AWAITS_YOU_AT                                                  = 10267,  -- Even I cannot ascertain what awaits you at the end of each path. Yet one must be chosen nonetheless.
        THIS_CHOICE_CANNOT_BE_AVOIDED                                                               = 10268,  -- This choice cannot be avoided...
        MY_DIVINATION_IS_AT_AN_END_HAVE_I                                                           = 10269,  -- ...My divination is at an end. Have I unsettled you?
        AHAHAHA_A_SEER_I_MAY_BE_BUT_I                                                               = 10270,  -- Ahahaha. A seer I may be, but I suggest you take these divinations with a light heart--no matter what the signs suggest.
        SHOULD_A_SIGN_PROVE_TO_BE_THE_GENTLE                                                        = 10271,  -- Should a sign prove to be the gentle push that was needed, then consider it a blessing.
        NOW_COMES_THE_MATTER_OF_PAYMENT_I_AM                                                        = 10272,  -- Now comes the matter of payment... I am told that an object of incredible rarity can be found in the Middle Lands.
        WOULD_YOU_CONSIDER_BRINGING_ME_THIS_PRIZE_IN                                                = 10273,  -- Would you consider bringing me this prize in place of common coin?
        TO_BE_TRUTHFUL_THE_ONE_WHO_WISHES_TO                                                        = 10274,  -- To be truthful, the one who wishes to gaze upon this object is my own bedridden mother. A final wish from a curious old lady...
        DO_NOT_CONCERN_YOURSELF_WITH_HASTE_MY_DEAR                                                  = 10275,  -- Do not concern yourself with haste. My dear mother clings to life with surprising ferocity.
        THE_OBJECT_OF_WHICH_I_SPEAK_IS_PRECIOUS                                                     = 10276,  -- The object of which I speak is precious in the Near East, but worth precious little elsewhere...
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS                                                       = 10277,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a jewel. It is said to glow with a bluish tint and be found near the bank of a certain river.
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS_2                                                     = 10278,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a jewel. It is said to glow with a bluish tint and be found near the bank of a certain river.
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS_3                                                     = 10279,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a pinch of golden sand. It is said to glow with the light of the sun and be found only on a certain beach.
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS_4                                                     = 10280,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a pinch of golden sand. It is said to glow with the light of the sun and be found only on a certain beach.
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS_5                                                     = 10281,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a precious stone. It is said to be as red as blood and found in a land of geysers.
        THE_TREASURE_I_WOULD_HAVE_YOU_SEEK_IS_6                                                     = 10282,  -- The treasure I would have you seek is a precious stone. It is said to be as red as blood and found in a land of geysers.
        THE_DISCOVERY_OF_THIS_OBJECT_IS_APPARENTLY_MADE                                             = 10283,  -- The discovery of this object is apparently made easier under very particular conditions, but I am not sufficiently familiar with the geography of your continent to even know where to start.
        I_CANNOT_PROVIDE_YOU_WITH_THE_NAME_OF                                                       = 10284,  -- I cannot provide you with the name of this treasure, but perhaps with your knowledge...
        MY_APOLOGIES_YOU_DO_NOT_NEED_TO_HEAR                                                        = 10285,  -- ...My apologies. You do not need to hear the woes of some street-corner fortuneteller.
        IN_FACT_I_SHALL_NOT_ASK_PAYMENT_OF                                                          = 10286,  -- In fact, I shall not ask payment of you this day. And please forget my unreasonable request. May fortune smile upon you...
        AH_YOU_HAVE_RETURNED_I_HOPE_YOU_HAVE                                                        = 10287,  -- Ah, you have returned. I hope you have forgotten our previous exchange. My words were hasty and ill-considered...
        YOUR_WORDS_HAVE_MOVED_ME_TO_ACTION_BEEN                                                     = 10288,  -- Your words have... ...moved me to action. ...been forgotten.
        ARE_YOU_SURE_OF_THIS_A_THOUSAND_THOUSAND                                                    = 10289,  -- Are you sure of this? A thousand thousand blessings on your house! I am speechless with gratitude...
        AGAIN_MY_APOLOGIES_I_KNOW_NOT_THE_NAME                                                      = 10290,  -- Again, my apologies! I know not the name of the object, but I do remember some clues...
        ITS_DISCOVERY_IS_APPARENTLY_MADE_EASIER_UNDER_VERY                                          = 10291,  -- Its discovery is apparently made easier under very particular conditions, but I cannot provide you with any details. My original source of information returned home to the Middle Lands before I could learn more.
        BUT_WITH_YOUR_KNOWLEDGE_OF_THAT_CONTINENT_YOU                                               = 10292,  -- But with your knowledge of that continent, you may have a chance...
        MAY_THE_WINDS_OF_FORTUNE_GUIDE_YOU_2                                                        = 10293,  -- May the winds of fortune guide you!
        I_KNOW_NOT_THE_NAME_OF_THE_OBJECT                                                           = 10294,  -- I know not the name of the object, but I do recall some clues...
        YES_THIS_IS_THE_WONDROUS_THE_TRAVELER_SPOKE                                                 = 10295,  -- Yes! This is the wondrous % the traveler spoke of!
        AH_3                                                                                        = 10296,  -- Ah...
        TO_BE_PERFECTLY_HONEST_IT_WAS_THE_MOTHER                                                    = 10297,  -- To be perfectly honest, it was the mother of a colleague who wished to gaze upon this treasure...
        I_AM_AFRAID_I_HAVE_ANOTHER_FAVOR_TO                                                         = 10298,  -- I am afraid I have another favor to ask you... Would you consent to deliver this to my colleague? I cannot leave the city, you see...
        A_THOUSAND_THOUSAND_APOLOGIES                                                               = 10299,  -- A thousand thousand apologies.
        MY_COLLEAGUE_IS_CURRENTLY_PART_OF_AN_IMPERIAL                                               = 10300,  -- My colleague is currently part of an Imperial patrol that apprehends desecrators of the ruins found in the Aydeewa Subterrane.
        THE_AYDEEWA_SUBTERRANE_RUNS_BENEATH_BHAFLAU_THICKETS_MAY                                    = 10301,  -- The Aydeewa Subterrane runs beneath Bhaflau Thickets. May the winds of fortune guide you.
        DEBUG_YOUR_COBALT_VALUE_IS_PERCENT                                                          = 10303,  -- DEBUG: Your cobalt value is # percent.
        DEBUG_YOUR_DIVINATION_RESULTS_ARE_NOW_BEYOND_THE                                            = 10304,  -- DEBUG: Your divination results are now beyond the realm of mortal men. Lucky you.
        YOU_HAD_NO_REASON_TO_RETURN_HERE                                                            = 10305,  -- You had no reason to return here...
        WHY_DO_YOU_STAND_BEFORE_ME                                                                  = 10306,  -- Why do you stand before me...?
        YOU_HAVE_MADE_THE_SACRIFICE_AND_JOINED_THE                                                  = 10307,  -- You have made the sacrifice and joined the ranks of the blue mages.
        WHAT_MORE_COULD_YOU_DESIRE_YOU_ARE_A                                                        = 10308,  -- What more could you desire? You are a vessel, newly made...
        HOW_YOU_FILL_THAT_VESSEL_IS_ENTIRELY_UP                                                     = 10309,  -- How you fill that vessel is entirely up to you.
        AS_YOU_PERFECT_THE_ARTS_OF_THE_BLUE                                                         = 10310,  -- As you perfect the arts of the blue mage, you will feel blue magic taking root in your very bones.
        HOWEVER_ATTEMPTING_TO_HARNESS_A_POWER_THAT_OVERFLOWS                                        = 10311,  -- However, attempting to harness a power that overflows your ability to hold it is a sure road to destruction...
        YOU_WOULD_DO_WELL_TO_REMEMBER_THAT                                                          = 10312,  -- You would do well to remember that.
        SO_WHAT_ARE_YOU_TO_DO                                                                       = 10313,  -- So what are you to do?
        HEHE_THE_ANSWER_IS_SIMPLE_GROW_IN_STRENGTH                                                  = 10314,  -- Hehe... The answer is simple. Grow in strength until your body can withstand the power you desire. The vessel you have become can be tempered and expanded.
        YOU_WERE_TOLD_A_BLUE_MAGE_MUST_WREST                                                        = 10315,  -- You were told: A blue mage must wrest his/her] strength and vitality from his/her] enemies.
        SHOW_ME_THE_DEPTHS_OF_YOUR_DESIRE_FOR                                                       = 10316,  -- Show me the depths of your desire for power...
        IF_YOU_CAN_UNCOVER_THE_STRENGTH_WITHIN_YOU                                                  = 10317,  -- If you can uncover the strength within you to rival my insight... ...But I have said too much.
        GO_FORTH_AND_DEVOUR_THE_ESSENCE_OF_YOUR                                                     = 10318,  -- %. Go forth and devour the essence of your foes.
        WELL_IF_IT_ISN_T_THE_POTENTIAL_NO                                                           = 10319,  -- Well, if it isn't the potential. No longer an empty vessel, I see.
        AND_YET_YOU_MAINTAIN_YOUR_MORTAL_FORM_IN                                                    = 10320,  -- And yet you maintain your mortal form in spite of the power you wield. Have you accepted the fact that the path of mortality is forever closed to you now?
        HAVE_YOU_ACCEPTED_THE_FACT_I_HAVE                                                           = 10321,  -- Have you accepted the fact? ... I have.
        WHAT_S_THIS_HAS_THE_SIMPLE_POWER_OF                                                         = 10322,  -- What's this? Has the simple power of speech abandoned you already?
        IT_IS_NOT_BEYOND_IMAGINING_YOU_HAVE_DEVOURED                                                = 10323,  -- It is not beyond imagining. You have devoured the essence of many foes--blue magic has unexpected effects on the practitioner.
        YOU_CANNOT_UNDO_THE_FLOW_OF_TIME_BE                                                         = 10324,  -- You cannot undo the flow of time. Be at ease. Let go of your regrets. I will show you the way.
        THERE_IS_NO_TURNING_BACK_YOU_MUST_TRAVEL                                                    = 10325,  -- %, there is no turning back. You must travel to the five staging points in search of even greater power.
        I_AM_GLAD_THAT_YOU_UNDERSTAND_YOUR_FATE                                                     = 10326,  -- I am glad that you understand your fate.
        IT_IS_TIME_FOR_YOU_TO_TRAVEL_TO                                                             = 10327,  -- It is time for you to travel to the five staging points in search of even greater power.
        AZOUPH_DVUCCA_MAMOOL_JA_HALVUNG_ILRUSI                                                      = 10328,  -- Azouph. Dvucca. Mamool Ja. Halvung. Ilrusi.
        THERE_YOU_WILL_FIND_YOUR_FELLOWS_THOSE_WHO                                                  = 10329,  -- There you will find your fellows--those who strive to be more than mortal while fending off the madness that erodes their souls.
        SOME_ARE_VESSELS_THAT_MERELY_MIMIC_THE_SHAPE                                                = 10330,  -- Some are vessels that merely mimic the shape of men and women, overflowing with savage energies...
        WHILE_OTHERS_HAVE_ACHIEVED_A_BALANCE_BETWEEN_THE                                            = 10331,  -- ...while others have achieved a balance between the nature of mortal and beast...
        THEY_HAVE_LONG_WALKED_THE_ROAD_YOU_NOW                                                      = 10332,  -- They have long walked the road you now stand upon.
        BURN_THEIR_LESSONS_INTO_YOUR_HEART_AND_FORGE                                                = 10333,  -- Burn their lessons into your heart, and forge your path with renewed vigor.
        FOR_NO_OTHER_PATHS_REMAIN_OPEN_TO_YOU                                                       = 10334,  -- For no other paths remain open to you...
        THE_SYMBOL_OF_GUIDANCE_FOUR_LAMPS_SURROUND_A                                                = 10335,  -- The symbol of guidance. Four lamps surround a mystical gate. The opening of this gate will lead you to distant lands.
        TO_THE_LAND_THAT_LIES_EAST_OF_NASHMAU                                                       = 10336,  -- To the land that lies east of Nashmau, beyond the Deadmist Marsh...
        TO_THE_LAND_THAT_LIES_WEST_OF_THE                                                           = 10337,  -- To the land that lies west of the city of Mamook...
        TO_THE_LAND_THAT_LIES_IN_THE_NORTHEASTERN                                                   = 10338,  -- To the land that lies in the northeastern shadow of Mount Zhayolm...
        TO_THE_LAND_THAT_LIES_WEST_ACROSS_THE                                                       = 10339,  -- To the land that lies west, across the sea from Nashmau...
        TO_THE_LAND_THAT_LIES_IN_THE_NORTHERN                                                       = 10340,  -- To the land that lies in the northern caverns of the Arrapago Reef...
        SO_YOU_HAVE_RETURNED_FROM_YOUR_JOURNEY                                                      = 10341,  -- So, you have returned from your journey.
        THE_IMMORTALS_HAVE_SUBMITTED_THEIR_REPORTS                                                  = 10342,  -- The Immortals have submitted their reports.
        MY_EVALUATION_YOU_ARE_STILL_NOT_FIT_TO                                                      = 10343,  -- My evaluation? You are still not fit to join our ranks.
        HOWEVER_I_WILL_RECOGNIZE_YOUR_CONTINUED_GROWTH_AND                                          = 10344,  -- However, I will recognize your continued growth and dedication.
        GREATER_HEIGHTS_OF_POWER_AWAIT_YOU_LET_THE                                                  = 10345,  -- Greater heights of power await you... Let the desire that burns within you guide your way.
        AMBITION_IS_THE_ONLY_FUEL_THAT_A_BLUE                                                       = 10346,  -- Ambition is the only fuel that a blue mage requires.
        YOU_HAVE_TAKEN_THE_FIRST_STEPS_BUT_THIS                                                     = 10347,  -- You have taken the first steps, but this is only the beginning.
        I_PRESENT_YOU_WITH_THIS_A_FITTING_BLADE                                                     = 10348,  -- I present you with this %, a fitting blade for the path you must carve.
        WIELD_IT_WELL                                                                               = 10349,  -- Wield it well.
        THE_PHENOMENON_ASSAULTING_YOU                                                               = 10350,  -- The phenomenon...assaulting you...
        IS_THE_RESULT_OF_THE_BLUE_MAGIC_INVADING                                                    = 10351,  -- ...is the result of...the blue magic...invading every cell...of your body...
        WHILE_YOUR_PHYSICAL_FORM_STRUGGLES_TO_CONTAIN_THIS                                          = 10352,  -- While your physical form...struggles to contain this energy, your soul is crying out in agony... The vessel that you have become has reached its limit.
        THIS_IS_MY_PRIVATE_DOMAIN_A_PLACE_SEPARATED                                                 = 10353,  -- This is my private domain--a place separated from the outside world through the power of the magic I have devoured. Here, isolated from reality, the state of a soul's deterioration is far more obvious.
        DO_YOU_LACK_EVEN_THE_STRENGTH_TO_STAND                                                      = 10354,  -- Do you lack even the strength to stand?
        YOU_MUST_HAVE_GORGED_YOURSELF_ON_THE_ESSENCE                                                = 10355,  -- You must have gorged yourself on the essence of your enemies to reach this condition.
        VERY_WELL_THE_DEPTHS_OF_YOUR_AMBITION_HAVE                                                  = 10356,  -- Very well. The depths of your ambition have been noted.
        IT_IS_NOT_FOR_ME_TO_PREVENT_YOUR                                                            = 10357,  -- It is not for me to prevent your self-destruction. Your limits are your own to conquer.
        A_RESILIENT_SPIRIT_TO_CONTROL_THE_FEAR_AND                                                  = 10358,  -- A resilient spirit to control the fear and allure aroused by the savage magic you devour... A willingness to discard your very self, should it lead to the achievement you desire...
        THESE_ARE_THE_QUALITIES_EVERY_BLUE_MAGE_MUST                                                = 10359,  -- These are the qualities every blue mage must possess.
        THERE_IS_NO_SALVATION_FOR_YOU_EITHER_YOU                                                    = 10360,  -- There is no salvation for you. Either you wait for oblivion to claim you, or continue to writhe within the energies of your foes. You stand at a fork in the road.
        LISTEN_WELL_SHOULD_YOU_DECIDE_ON_A_LIFE                                                     = 10361,  -- Listen well, %. Should you decide on a life consumed with the struggle for power, I can show you the path...
        TRAVEL_TO_THE_NAVUKGO_EXECUTION_CHAMBER_AND_DESTROY                                         = 10362,  -- Travel to the Navukgo Execution Chamber, and destroy the flan that are resisting the Imperial Army.
        A_SIMPLE_TASK_FOR_A_SEASONED_BLUE_MAGE                                                      = 10363,  -- A simple task for a seasoned blue mage--not so simple for you, perhaps...
        BE_TEMPERED_BY_THE_OBSTACLES_YOU_OVERCOME_SHOW                                              = 10364,  -- Be tempered by the obstacles you overcome. Show me the strength of your will.
        THE_SYMBOL_OF_TRIALS_TRAVERSE_THE_DEAD_FIELDS                                               = 10365,  -- The symbol of trials... Traverse the dead fields where no plant or animal thrives. You will find your destination beyond the sea of fire.
        THE_BEASTS_LEFT_BEHIND_WHEN_THE_VESSEL_IS                                                   = 10366,  -- The beasts left behind when the vessel is shattered...
        I_HAVE_JUST_RECEIVED_A_REPORT_FROM_THE                                                      = 10367,  -- I have just received a report from the Imperial Army on the success of your task. Your skills as a blue mage are to be commended.
        IN_RECOGNITION_OF_THIS_ACHIEVEMENT_I_GIVE_YOU                                               = 10368,  -- In recognition of this achievement, I give you leave to don the magus armor representative of our order.
        THIS_MARKS_YOUR_ENTRANCE_INTO_THE_RANKS_OF                                                  = 10369,  -- This marks your entrance into the ranks of the Immortals. Congratulations, %.
        VISIT_THE_STORE_NAMED_ON_THIS_ENVELOPE_AND                                                  = 10370,  -- Visit the store named on this envelope and receive the armor you have earned.
        DO_NOT_FORGET_OUR_LIVES_ARE_DEVOTED_TO                                                      = 10371,  -- Do not forget: our lives are devoted to the protection of the Empress. Nothing more, nothing less.
        WE_ARE_BEASTS_THAT_OWE_OUR_EXISTENCE_TO                                                     = 10372,  -- We are beasts that owe our existence to the forbearance of Her Magnificence...
        THE_SYMBOL_OF_ENCOUNTERS_THE_TWO_HEADED_SERPENT                                             = 10373,  -- The symbol of encounters... The two-headed serpent will open the way.
        WHAT_CAN_I_DO_FOR_YOU                                                                       = 10374,  -- What can I do for you?
        WHA_THE_M_MARK_OF_ZAHAK                                                                     = 10375,  -- Wha-!? The M-Mark of Zahak!
        Y_YOU_YOU_RE_AN_IMMORTAL                                                                    = 10376,  -- Y-you...you're an Immortal?
        OH_MY_A_THOUSAND_PARDONS_A_THOUSAND_THOUSAND                                                = 10377,  -- Oh my! A thousand pardons! A thousand thousand pardons! You see, the master craftsman...he's...he's not here... Your armor is not...it's not ready...
        I_M_WELL_YOU_CAN_SEE_HOW_IT                                                                 = 10378,  -- I'm, well...you can see how it is. Even if I knew where he had gone, I couldn't follow... My boss knew this was coming--he has a cruel streak, I fear.
        IT_ALWAYS_FALLS_TO_ME_TO_APOLOGIZE_TO                                                       = 10379,  -- It always falls to me to apologize to the customers...
        WHAT_S_THAT_YOU_WANT_TO_KNOW_WHERE                                                          = 10380,  -- What's that? You want to know where he's gone?
        MY_M_MOST_HUMBLE_APOLOGIES_WHEN_THE_ORDERS                                                  = 10381,  -- My m-most humble apologies. When the orders start piling up, my boss goes fishing. Runs away is perhaps a more fitting term. The problem is, he doesn't go to the sea, or to a river...
