        VERY_WELL_THEN_LET_US_PROCEED_ON_TO                                                         = 14567,  -- Very well, then. Let us proceed on to more urgent matters.
        SURELY_YOU_STILL_RECALL_THE_WEAPON_WHICH_YOU                                                = 14568,  -- Surely you still recall the weapon which you entrusted to the safekeeping of one Naja Salaheem? The same instrument which you extracted from the ruined depths of Nyzul Isle.
        THAT_WEAPON_WAS_NONE_OTHER_THAN_ONE_OF                                                      = 14569,  -- That weapon was none other than one of the fabled vigil weapons, fashioned to be vessels of a great protective force.
        THE_VIGIL_WEAPONS_WERE_KEPT_WITHIN_THE_IMPERIAL                                             = 14570,  -- The vigil weapons were kept within the Imperial Treasury, placed in lush ceremony atop their sealed counterparts, the mythic weapons. In this state, the polar natures of the weapons achieved a perfect balance, and were thus able to be contained.
        THE_MYTHIC_WEAPONS_ARE_AN_UNPARALLELED_COLLECTION_OF                                        = 14571,  -- The mythic weapons are an unparalleled collection of arms amassed by the hero of our Empire, the mighty Balrahn, as he journeyed in the four directions felling fierce and countless opponents and brought his greatness to bear upon Vana'diel.
        THESE_ARE_THE_TRUE_TREASURES_OF_AHT_URHGAN                                                  = 14572,  -- These are the true Treasures of Aht Urhgan.
        IN_ADDITION_TO_THE_MIRACULOUS_PROPERTIES_ATTRIBUTED_TO                                      = 14573,  -- In addition to the miraculous properties attributed to them, the weapons were also objects of undying affection for Balrahn.
        IT_WAS_NOT_LONG_BEFORE_HIS_OBSESSION_WITH                                                   = 14574,  -- It was not long before his obsession with them had grown to maniacal heights, and he continued to seek out new additions for his collection tirelessly.
        OF_COURSE_THE_NATURES_OF_THE_WEAPONS_WERE                                                   = 14575,  -- Of course, the natures of the weapons were simply too vast to be harnessed and treated as mere museum pieces.
        THEREFORE_HE_COMMISSIONED_HIS_MASTER_OF_CEREMONIES_TO                                       = 14576,  -- Therefore, he commissioned his Master of Ceremonies to see to the creation of the vigil weapons in a desperate attempt to diminish the raw power of the mythic weapons so that they might be tamed.
        SINCE_THEN_IT_HAS_BEEN_THE_CHARGE_OF                                                        = 14577,  -- Since then, it has been the charge of the Master of Ceremonies to oversee the safekeeping of the mythic weapons. But...
        FOLLOWING_THE_THEFT_OF_THE_VIGIL_WEAPONS_FROM                                               = 14578,  -- Following the theft of the vigil weapons from the Imperial Treasury, the power of the mythic weapons began to grow unchecked. Even now, should the vigil weapons be returned, I fear it is too late to reharness what has been unleashed.
        AND_SO_WE_ARE_LEFT_WITH_BUT_ONE                                                             = 14579,  -- And so we are left with but one recourse.
        ONLY_BY_FINDING_ONE_WITH_THE_VIRTUE_AND                                                     = 14580,  -- Only by finding one with the virtue and strength of our great Balrahn to bend the spirit of the mythic weapons to their will may we return them to their peaceful slumber deep in the undisturbed corners of the Imperial coffers.
        IT_WAS_TO_THIS_END_THAT_WE_SOUGHT                                                           = 14581,  -- It was to this end that we sought to employ your services, %.
        WE_WERE_WARNED_BY_HER_MAJESTY_S_GREAT                                                       = 14582,  -- We were warned by her Majesty's great uncle, Zarafeehl, that the dangers of entrusting the fate of these weapons to one not born of the Empire was an unwise risk fraught with dangers.
        BUT_WE_WERE_UNWAVERED_IN_OUR_CONFIDENCE_IN                                                  = 14583,  -- But we were unwavered in our confidence in you. And so to sway Zarafeehl, we set to you these most heroic of tasks, all of which you have accomplished.
        WE_BEG_YOUR_INDULGENCE_AND_YOUR_FORGIVENESS_BUT                                             = 14584,  -- We beg your indulgence, and your forgiveness, %. But please try to understand the desperate position into which we were thrust.
        AND_YET_I_M_AFRAID_WE_HAVE_STILL                                                            = 14585,  -- And yet, I'm afraid we have still more to ask of you. We would like to place the mythic weapon, %, in your care, %.
        YOUR_EFFORTS_HAVE_LED_US_TO_BELIEVE_THAT                                                    = 14586,  -- Your efforts have led us to believe that you may indeed be able to resist the overwhelming temptation of the power this weapon contains.
        A_TASK_FOR_NONE_OTHER_THAN_THE_TRUE                                                         = 14587,  -- A task for none other than the true guardian of the Empire!
        THANK_YOU_THANK_YOU                                                                         = 14588,  -- Thank you, %... Thank you.
        BEHOLD_THIS_IS                                                                              = 14589,  -- Behold! This is %.
        AND_IT_IS_NOW_YOURS_BY_RIGHT_AND                                                            = 14590,  -- And it is now yours by right and rule!
        DO_BE_CAREFUL_I_DO_NOT_DOUBT_IN                                                             = 14591,  -- Do be careful, %. I do not doubt in the power of your will. But should you succumb in even the slightest to the allure of that weapon...
        SO_IT_IS_DONE_THE_EMPRESS_MUST_NOW                                                          = 14592,  -- So it is done. The Empress must now see to informing Zarafeehl of what has transpired here today. We beg your pardon.
        HMPH_UNTIL_WE_MEET_AGAIN_THEN                                                               = 14593,  -- Hmph. Until we meet again, then, %.
        ID_14594                                                                                    = 14594,  -- ...
