        THAT_SOUNDS_ABOUT_RIGHT_HERE_YOU_GO_THEN                                                    = 14645,  -- That sounds about right. Here you go, then, # shiny %, just for you! Don't spend it all in one place!
        PRESIDENT_NAJA_SURELY_YOU_DON_T_MEAN_TO                                                     = 14646,  -- President Naja, surely you don't mean to--
        I_THINK_I_VE_GROWN_QUITE_SICK_OF                                                            = 14647,  -- I think I've grown quite sick of that title, Abquhbah. From now on I think I'll have you address me as something more appropriate. Say...
        HER_ROYAL_HIGHNESS_OF_FRUGALITY_AND_THRIFT_HOW                                              = 14648,  -- Her Royal Highness of Frugality and Thrift! How does the sound of that strike you?
        YOU_VE_GOT_TO_BE_KIDDING                                                                    = 14649,  -- You've got to be kidding...
        OH_WOE_IS_ME_OH_GLOOM_AND_MISERY                                                            = 14650,  -- Oh, woe is me! Oh, gloom and misery!
        OH_HULLO_THERE_IF_IT_ISN_T_MY                                                               = 14651,  -- Oh, hullo there. If it isn't my erstwhile attendant. Well met...
        COME_TO_HAVE_A_JEST_HAVE_YOU_TO                                                             = 14652,  -- Come to have a jest, have you? To jape and jeer at Fari-Wari the Pitiful?
        ONCE_THE_ACCLAIMED_BALLADEER_OF_THE_SERPENT_GENERALS                                        = 14653,  -- Once the acclaimed balladeer of the Serpent Generals five--or was it four? Bah, 'tis no matter.
        A_MINSTREL_OF_SUCH_REPUTE_THAT_OTHER_BARDS                                                  = 14654,  -- A minstrel of such repute that other bards would sing my praises! My adoring fans lined up on every corner to catch a passing strain of my latest magnum opus!
        WHAT_S_THE_MATTER_YOU_SAY_SEE_FOR                                                           = 14655,  -- What's the matter, you say!? See for yourself!
        IMITATION_IS_THE_SINCEREST_FORM_OF_FLATTERY_HOGWASH                                         = 14656,  -- Imitation is the sincerest form of flattery? Hogwash, I say!
        THOSE_HACKS_THOSE_POSEURS_THEY_PILFER_MY_MELODIES                                           = 14657,  -- Those hacks, those poseurs! They pilfer my melodies and claim them as their own! And do you know the worst of it, my dear attendant?
        THE_UNCULTURED_HOI_POLLOI_THEY_PAY_NO_HEED                                                  = 14658,  -- The uncultured hoi polloi--they pay no heed to this artistic travesty! They suck up this swill like so many swine!
        AHEM_PARDON_ME                                                                              = 14659,  -- <Ahem> Pardon me...
        OH_WOE_IS_THERE_NO_ONE_IN_THIS                                                              = 14660,  -- Oh, woe! Is there no one in this boorish world who can appreciate true genius!? Is this how the ballad of Fari-Wari is destined to close? A melancholy coda to a once-glorious career? The tragedy! The horror!
        AH_SO_YOU_RE_FARI_WARI_YOUR_REPUTATION                                                      = 14661,  -- Ah, so you're Fari-Wari. Your reputation for bombast precedes you.
        THAT_WOULD_MAKE_YOU_CORRECT                                                                 = 14662,  -- That would make you %, correct?
        YES_YES_MY_HAPLESS_ATTENDANT_SHOULD_YOU_HAVE                                                = 14663,  -- Yes, yes...my hapless attendant. Should you have business with us, please direct your inquiries to the management--namely, me.
        I_SEE_AS_A_MATTER_OF_FACT_I                                                                 = 14664,  -- I see. As a matter of fact, I was hoping to obtain your counsel--
        DENIED                                                                                      = 14665,  -- Denied!
        IF_YOU_COULD_NOT_DISCERN_FROM_MY_DAPPER                                                     = 14666,  -- If you could not discern from my dapper attire and most mellifluous voice, I am a bard, you see? I have neither the time nor the inclination to entertain the trifling sob stories of every wastrel in town. If an ear for your bellyaching is all you seek, I suggest you order yourself a chai and chat up the proprietor of this establishment!
        AS_YOU_WISH_MASTER_FARI_WARI_I_SHALL                                                        = 14667,  -- As you wish, Master Fari-Wari. I shall find another ear for the matter of General Gadalar.
        YES_YES_AWAY_WITH_YOU_AH_BEGGING_YOUR                                                       = 14668,  -- Yes yes, away with you--ah. Begging your pardon, my good man, but did you say General Gadalar? You speak of the Flameserpent General?
        THE_VERY_SAME_AS_YOU_MIGHT_KNOW_GENERAL                                                     = 14669,  -- The very same. As you might know, General Gadalar is...how shall I put it? A tad...impulsive? Volatile, if you will?
        NO_EXPLANATION_NEEDED_MY_FRIEND_I_M_STILL                                                   = 14670,  -- No explanation needed, my friend! I'm still smoldering from the time he unleashed a Firaga spell on my delicate derriere...the rogue!
        OH_MY_THAT_DOES_SOUND_MOST_HARROWING_NOW                                                    = 14671,  -- Oh my, that does sound most harrowing. Now, if I may continue... Needless to say, the Flameserpent General's...contentious...behavior has not gone unnoticed by high command.
        TO_THIS_POINT_HIS_UNDENIABLE_PROWESS_IN_BATTLE                                              = 14672,  -- To this point, his undeniable prowess in battle and the personal good graces of the Skyserpent General have shielded him from being seriously punished for his indiscretions.
        THIS_TIME_HOWEVER_THE_POWERS_THAT_BE_HAVE                                                   = 14673,  -- This time, however, the powers that be have lost their patience and decided to court-martial him for his actions! I fear that there may be no saving him.
        HOW_TERRIBLY_UNFORTUNATE_COULDN_T_HAVE_HAPPENED_TO                                          = 14674,  -- How terribly unfortunate. Couldn't have happened to a nicer chap, I say!
        TIS_TRUE_THAT_GENERAL_GADALAR_S_PRICKLY_DEMEANOR                                            = 14675,  -- 'Tis true that General Gadalar's prickly demeanor has not endeared him to his superiors. Even in the halls of the Imperial Court, few are willing to step forward in his defense.
        HIS_FELLOW_SERPENT_GENERALS_ARE_EXERTING_THEIR_BEST                                         = 14676,  -- His fellow Serpent Generals are exerting their best efforts on his behalf, but...
        TO_NO_AVAIL                                                                                 = 14677,  -- To no avail?
        SADLY_NO_AND_GENERAL_GADALAR_S_REFUSAL_TO                                                   = 14678,  -- Sadly, no. And General Gadalar's refusal to exercise even a modicum of self-restraint has served only to fan the flames.
        ON_THE_CONTRARY_THE_LATEST_RUMORS_HAVE_IT                                                   = 14679,  -- On the contrary, the latest rumors have it that he has taken to slipping outside the city walls under the veil of night. On what furtive errand, no one knows.
        OUTSIDE_TOWN_HOW_CURIOUS_INDEED_OHO_MAYHAP_HE                                               = 14680,  -- Outside town? How curious indeed... Oho! Mayhap he's merely partaking in a tryst or two with his latest inamorata?
        PREPOSTEROUS_THE_FLAMESERPENT_GENERAL_IS_NOT_ONE_FOR                                        = 14681,  -- Preposterous! The Flameserpent General is not one for idle romance.
        ON_ANOTHER_SUBJECT_HAVE_YOU_PERCHANCE_HEARD_THE                                             = 14682,  -- On another subject, have you perchance heard the news of The Crow of the East?
        CROW_I_THOUGHT_WE_WERE_DISCUSSING_THE_GENERAL                                               = 14683,  -- Crow? I thought we were discussing the General Gadalar, not some vile bird. Though if we must speak of eastern fowl, they say there's one called a pheasant that tastes most delectable in a fine currant sauce.
        I_SPEAK_NOT_OF_BIRDS_BUT_RATHER_BIRDMEN                                                     = 14684,  -- I speak not of birds, but rather birdmen. Beastmen of the Far East.
        HAVE_YOU_NOT_HEARD_THE_WHISPERS_MEMBERS_OF                                                  = 14685,  -- Have you not heard the whispers? Members of the night watch have come under attack from an unidentified foe...
        THE_DETAILS_REMAIN_CLOSELY_GUARDED_BUT_WITNESSES_HAVE                                       = 14686,  -- The details remain closely guarded, but witnesses have stated that the culprit bears an uncanny resemblance to a birdman of the east.
        BIRDMAN_AH_A_YAGUDO                                                                         = 14687,  -- Birdman? Ah, a Yagudo!
        AND_SINCE_GENERAL_GADALAR_SPENT_SO_MANY_YEARS                                               = 14688,  -- And since General Gadalar spent so many years stationed in the Far East, they suspect him of being in league with this fiend?
        SADLY_YES                                                                                   = 14689,  -- Sadly, yes.
        NOW_TIS_TRUE_THAT_THE_FLAMESERPENT_GENERAL_S                                                = 14690,  -- Now, 'tis true that the Flameserpent General's cavalier demeanor might lead some to believe he is not as responsible as his peers.
        YET_AS_HIS_ADJUTANT_I_SWEAR_TO_YOU                                                          = 14691,  -- Yet, as his adjutant, I swear to you on my life. The general's love of nation and sense of duty are second to no man.
        THE_IDEA_THAT_HE_WOULD_STRIKE_DOWN_A                                                        = 14692,  -- The idea that he would strike down a comrade in cold blood is inconceivable!
        OHO_8                                                                                       = 14693,  -- Oho...
        SO_I_TURN_TO_THE_TWO_OF_YOU                                                                 = 14694,  -- So I turn to the two of you. I have heard that you are trusted by the Serpent Generals. Surely you could approach General Gadalar without arousing undue suspicion.
        FRIENDS_OF_THE_EMPIRE_I_BESEECH_YOU_FIND                                                    = 14695,  -- Friends of the Empire, I beseech you. Find proof of the general's innocence before the court-martial commences and our worst fears are realized.
        NO_SMALL_TASK                                                                               = 14696,  -- No small task...
        BUT_WE_ACCEPT_LET_IT_NEVER_BE_SAID                                                          = 14697,  -- ...but we accept! Let it never be said that Fari-Wari the Courageous and his plucky attendant would turn a blind eye to one in need!
        TRULY_YOU_LL_HELP_I_CANNOT_THANK_YOU                                                        = 14698,  -- Truly, you'll help? I cannot thank you enough!
        THE_GENERAL_S_BEEN_OBSERVED_HEADING_IN_THE                                                  = 14699,  -- The general's been observed heading in the direction of Mount Zhayolm.
        AH_YES_MOUNT_ZHAYOLM_QUITE_A_TREK_FROM                                                      = 14700,  -- Ah, yes...Mount Zhayolm. Quite a trek from here, and crawling with all manner of unpleasant Trolls...
        THIS_SOUNDS_LIKE_JUST_THE_TASK_FOR_MY                                                       = 14701,  -- This sounds like just the task for...my loyal attendant!
        OH_HO_BUT_I_JEST_THOUGHT_YOU_D                                                              = 14702,  -- Oh ho, but I jest! Thought you'd be left to fend for yourself while Fari-Wari sits around sipping chai, did you?
        NOT_THIS_TIME_MY_FRIEND_AFTER_ALL_NO                                                        = 14703,  -- Not this time, my friend! After all, no enterprising bard could pass up a prime chance to get some dirt on-- ...er, that is, to earn the favor of the incomparable General Gadalar.
        AND_IN_THE_PROCESS_EXACT_MY_REVENGE_FOR                                                     = 14704,  -- And, in the process, exact my revenge for-- ...ahem, rather, acquire some prime material for my next lyrical masterpiece. Heh heh heh...
        I_SEE_IN_ANY_EVENT_THE_FLAMESERPENT_GENERAL                                                 = 14705,  -- I see... In any event, the Flameserpent General's fate is in your hands. Pray report back to me as soon as your investigation bears fruit.
        SAY_NO_MORE                                                                                 = 14706,  -- Say no more!
        WITH_FARI_WARI_ON_THE_JOB_THE_DEED                                                          = 14707,  -- With Fari-Wari on the job, the deed is as good as done. You heard the good man, %. We're off to Mount Zhayolm!
        WE_LL_RENDEZVOUS_AT_THE_PATH_LEADING_TO                                                     = 14708,  -- We'll rendezvous at the path leading to Halvung. Last one there is a rotten puk egg!
        AH_TOOK_YOU_LONG_ENOUGH_I_WAS_BEGINNING                                                     = 14709,  -- Ah, %...took you long enough. I was beginning to worry that you'd fallen into a crater.
        I_VE_BEEN_WAITING_HERE_FOR_SHAYADAR_BUT                                                     = 14710,  -- I've been waiting here for Shayadar, but it would appear that our friend is a busy man.
        OH_YOU_RE_HERE_THANK_THE_HEAVENS                                                            = 14711,  -- Oh, you're here! Thank the heavens!
        AH_SHAYADAR_WE_VE_BEEN_WAITING_SO_LONG                                                      = 14712,  -- Ah, Shayadar. We've been waiting so long we were starting to grow moss. You seem flustered. Whatever is the matter?
        FRIENDS_I_BRING_GRAVE_NEWS_THE_OFFICER_IN                                                   = 14713,  -- Friends, I bring grave news. The officer in charge of Gadalar's court-martial, one General Malzaab, has lost his patience. He's ordered for the committee to convene ahead of schedule!
        GENERAL_RUGHADJEEN_YOU_AND_I_ARE_BOTH_BUSY                                                  = 14714,  -- General Rughadjeen, you and I are both busy men. How much longer does he intend to keep us waiting?
        I_ASSURE_YOU_GENERAL_NAJELITH_HAS_BEEN_SENT                                                 = 14715,  -- I assure you, General Najelith has been sent to escort him here as we speak. Pray abide for just a moment longer, sir.
        THIS_IS_PREPOSTEROUS_THE_MAN_CANNOT_FIND_HIS                                                = 14716,  -- This is preposterous. The man cannot find his way to our chambers without a Serpent General as his personal chaperone? Perhaps he avoids us because he has something to hide, hm?
        NEVER_GENERAL_GADALAR_MAY_BE_HOTHEADED_YES_BUT                                              = 14717,  -- Never! General Gadalar may be hotheaded, yes, but surely you know as well as I that he is among our most exemplary warriors!
        IT_IS_NOT_HIS_MARTIAL_ABILITIES_THAT_WE                                                     = 14718,  -- It is not his martial abilities that we doubt, General Rughadjeen. His brilliant exploits on the Far Eastern front have not been forgotten. On the contrary, it is because we hold him in such high regard that we negotiated for him to be first among the hostages freed from captivity.
        STILL_NO_AMOUNT_OF_SUCCESS_IN_BATTLE_PLACES                                                 = 14719,  -- Still, no amount of success in battle places one above the law. All the more so for a general of the Imperial Army.
        ID_14720                                                                                    = 14720,  -- ...
        SINCE_YOUR_FRIEND_CLEARLY_HAS_NO_RESPECT_FOR                                                = 14721,  -- Since your friend clearly has no respect for our time, let us use it productively. Solicitor, if you will.
        YES_SIR_OYEZ_OYEZ_OYEZ_THE_CHARGES_AGAINST                                                  = 14722,  -- Yes, sir. Oyez, oyez, oyez! The charges against the Flameserpent General are as follows...
        FIRSTLY_STRIKING_THE_DEFENSELESS_GENERAL_ANIZAHM_WITH_AN                                    = 14723,  -- Firstly, striking the defenseless General Anizahm with an armored fist during a verbal dispute at last month's war council. The blow broke multiple teeth and put the general out of commission for nigh a month.
        ID_14724                                                                                    = 14724,  -- ...
        NEXT                                                                                        = 14725,  -- Next!
        FURTHERMORE_INDISCRIMINATE_BRANDISHING_OF_HIS_SCYTHE_AND_WIELDING                           = 14726,  -- Furthermore, indiscriminate brandishing of his scythe and wielding of destructive magic during a quarrel with mercenaries at a public teahouse. These actions caused over 400 Imperial gold pieces worth of property damages, not to mention needlessly endangering the lives of innocent bystanders.
        ID_14727                                                                                    = 14727,  -- ...
        YES_SIR_AHEM                                                                                = 14728,  -- Yes, sir. <Ahem>...
        LASTLY_IS_THE_MATTER_AT_THE_CORE_OF                                                         = 14729,  -- Lastly is the matter at the core of these proceedings. We have strong reason to suspect that General Gadalar, with his connections to the Far East, is working in league with the Yagudo spies that have been sighted within the city. Eyewitness reports place--
        WE_HAVE_REASON_TO_SUSPECT_THAT_AN_OFFICER                                                   = 14730,  -- We have reason to suspect that an officer with close ties to the East is working in league with this foul beastman. Clearly, this points to the Flameserp--
        PREPOSTEROUS_GENERAL_GADALAR_WOULD_NEVER                                                    = 14731,  -- Preposterous! General Gadalar would never...!
        A_K_M_CCHJ                                                                                  = 14732,  -- %A K_+M\>)ccHj
        GRIEVOUS_NEWS_AH                                                                            = 14733,  -- Grievous news! Ah...
        PRAY_EXCUSE_US_FOR_A_MOMENT                                                                 = 14734,  -- Pray excuse us for a moment.
        WHAT_S_GOING_ON_WHERE_IS_GADALAR                                                            = 14735,  -- What's going on? Where is Gadalar!?
        GENERAL_RUGHADJEEN_I_WAS_PREPARED_TO_BRING_HIM                                              = 14736,  -- General Rughadjeen, I was prepared to bring him here bound hand and foot if necessary. But I've searched his quarters--he's nowhere to be found!
        NO_DOUBT_HE_S_TAKEN_UMBRAGE_AT_THE                                                          = 14737,  -- No doubt he's taken umbrage at the very notion of these proceedings...
        BUT_WHATEVER_SHALL_WE_DO_IF_HE_ANGERS                                                       = 14738,  -- But whatever shall we do? If he angers the committee, he could lose his position...!
        OR_HIS_HEAD                                                                                 = 14739,  -- ...Or his head.
        MY_DEEPEST_APOLOGIES_IT_APPEARS_THAT_GENERAL_GADALAR                                        = 14740,  -- My deepest apologies. It appears that General Gadalar is abed with a fever most foul, and will be unable to present himself today.
        BWAHAHAHA_DOES_HE_TAKE_US_FOR_FOOLS_THE                                                     = 14741,  -- Bwahahaha! Does he take us for fools? The mighty Flameserpent General bedridden with a mere fever?
        I_ASK_YOU_PUT_OFF_THE_PROCEEDINGS_FOR                                                       = 14742,  -- I ask you, put off the proceedings for another day. Next time, I swear on my honor, I will bring Gadalar here myself.
        AS_YOU_WISH_FAR_BE_IT_FROM_ME                                                               = 14743,  -- As you wish. Far be it from me to deny a heartfelt plea from the Skyserpent General. Next time, though, there will be no excuses.
        SURELY_YOU_SEE_THE_URGENCY_OF_THE_SITUATION                                                 = 14744,  -- Surely you see the urgency of the situation. We must find General Gadalar at all costs.
        OF_COURSE_EVEN_IF_FOUND_TIS_UNLIKELY_HE                                                     = 14745,  -- Of course, even if found, 'tis unlikely he'll go willingly. Alas! Is there nothing that can be done? <Sigh>...
        SHAYADAR_MY_GOOD_MAN_PARDON_FOR_INTERRUPTING_YOUR                                           = 14746,  -- Shayadar, my good man. Pardon for interrupting your brooding, but as a matter of fact, my attendant and I...
        WHAT_S_THIS_YOU_SAY_GENERAL_GADALAR_ASSAULTED                                               = 14747,  -- What's this you say? General Gadalar assaulted you at Mount Zhayolm? Surely...surely the accusations aren't--
        NO_THEY_CANNOT_THEY_MUST_NOT_BE_TRUE                                                        = 14748,  -- No, they cannot--they must not--be true! General Gadalar would never...
        I_EOE5_CCB                                                                                  = 14749,  -- {I%eOE5=ccB
        WAIT_2                                                                                      = 14750,  -- ...Wait.
        YOU_WITNESSED_THE_FLAMESERPENT_GENERAL_S_ACTIONS_FOR                                        = 14751,  -- You witnessed the Flameserpent General's actions for only a decidedly short period of time, correct?
        WELL_YES_WE_DID_LOSE_SIGHT_OF_HIM                                                           = 14752,  -- Well, yes. We did lose sight of him halfway through--
        COULD_IT_BE_THAT_YOU_WERE_SET_UP                                                            = 14753,  -- Could it be that you were set up as a witness?
        WH_WHAT                                                                                     = 14754,  -- Wh-what!?
        IF_THAT_WAS_TRULY_ALL_GENERAL_GADALAR_S                                                     = 14755,  -- If that was truly all General Gadalar's doing, it is almost as if he wanted to be seen. But for what purpose...?
        P_9F_F5_N_Q6AH_I1FP_R5DCCB                                                                  = 14756,  -- _p+9f$F5=N)%(*%q6aH")%=?*%i1Fp#%R5DccB
        INDEED_IF_ONLY_WE_HAD_SOME_OTHER_CLUE                                                       = 14757,  -- Indeed. If only we had some other clue...
        OH_HOW_COULD_I_FORGET_WE_FOUND_THIS                                                         = 14758,  -- Oh, how could I forget!? We found this at the scene. Perhaps this sheds some light on the Flameserpent General's actions?
        IS_THIS                                                                                     = 14759,  -- Is this...%?
        IT_S_A_RARE_AND_HIGHLY_VALUABLE_FLOWER                                                      = 14760,  -- It's a rare and highly valuable flower that grows only in the Far East...or so I've heard.
        WHY_WOULD_GENERAL_GADALAR_CARELESSLY_TOSS_ASIDE_SUCH                                        = 14761,  -- Why would General Gadalar carelessly toss aside such a precious blossom? Perhaps it is a signal of sorts? Some cryptic message, known only to those of the East?
        I_M_AFRAID_THAT_WITHOUT_MORE_EVIDENCE_TIS                                                   = 14762,  -- I'm afraid that without more evidence, 'tis naught but idle speculation. I beseech you, friends. Will you return to Mount Zhayolm and hunt down the truth?
        BUT_OF_COURSE_MY_GOOD_MAN_FARI_WARI                                                         = 14763,  -- But of course, my good man! Fari-Wari the Fastidious is not one to leave a job half-done!
